 ERJ family|Embraer ERJ-145]]\n|4\n|0\n|30\n|-\n|}<br />\n\n== Interline Partners ==\nIn November 2019, Contour launched an interline agreement with [[American Airlines]]. Passengers can now travel via Contour and American under a single itinerary. \n\n<br />\n\n== In-flight Experience ==\nPassengers traveling with Contour receive free seat selection and first piece of checked baggage with all fare classes.<ref> https://www.contourairlines.com/en-us/plan-your-trip/baggage#baggage-policy </ref> All Contour flights feature leather seating, 36 inches of legroom, and complimentary in-flight snack and beverage service.<ref> https://calendar.in.gov/site/iedc/event/iedc-indiana-lands-new-airline-base-for-indy-airport-new-nonstop-routes-jobs--future-growth/ </ref>  \n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n[https://www.contourairlines.com/en Official website]\n\n{{Airlines of the United States}}\n\n[[Category:Airlines of the United States]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Tennessee]]\n[[Category:Airlines established in 1982]]\n[[Category:1982 establishments in Tennessee]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Airline\n| airline = Contour Airlines\n| logo = Contour Final.png\n| logo_size = \n| fleet_size = 14\n| destinations = 18<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.contourairlines.com/en/destinations|title=ContourAirlines|website=www.contourairlines.com|language=en|access-date=2018-03-29}}</ref>\n| IATA = LF\n| ICAO = VTE\n| callsign = VOLUNTEER\n| parent = [[Contour Aviation]]\n| company_slogan = \n| founded = 2016\n| commenced = March 22, 2016\n| headquarters = [[Smyrna, Tennessee]], U.S.\n| key_people = Matt Chaifetz, CEO<br><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://contouraviation.com/about-cfm/|title=About Corporate Flight Management - CFM|work=Contour Aviation|access-date=2018-03-29|language=en-US}}</ref>\n| hubs = \n| secondary_hubs = \n| focus_cities = <div>\n*[[Indianapolis International Airport]]<ref>https://www.aviationpros.com/airlines/press-release/21124857/indiana-lands-new-airline-base-for-indianapolis-airport-new-nonstop-routes-jobs-and-future-growth</ref>\n*[[Santa Barbara Municipal Airport]]<ref>https://www.aviationpros.com/airlines/press-release/21045400/contour-airlines-selects-santa-barbara-as-focus-city</ref>\n| frequent_flyer = \n| lounge = \n| alliance = \n| website = [http://www.contourairlines.com/ contourairlines.com]\n| image = \n| aoc = \n| num_employees = \n}}\n'''Contour Airlines''' is a [[regional airline]] headquartered at [[Smyrna Airport (Tennessee)|Smyrna Airport]] in [[Smyrna, Tennessee]], United States.<ref name=\"FI\">{{cite news|title=Directory: World Airlines|date=2007-04-03|work=[[Flight International]]|page=69}}</ref> All Contour Airlines flights are public charters sold and operated by parent company [[Contour Aviation]] as a direct carrier. \n\n==History==\n[[File:N11526 BWI MD1.jpg|thumb|Contour Airlines ERJ-135LR at Baltimore-Washington Thurgood Marshall Airport]]\nContour Airlines was established by parent company Contour Aviation in 2016. Contour began service on March 22, 2016, completing its inaugural flight from Nashville to Tupelo, Mississippi. Since then, Contour has expanded to 20 destinations nationwide, focusing on providing key business and leisure markets previously underserved nonstop short haul routes.<ref> https://calendar.in.gov/site/iedc/event/iedc-indiana-lands-new-airline-base-for-indy-airport-new-nonstop-routes-jobs--future-growth/</ref> \n\nOn April 1, 2019, Contour retired its Jetstream 31/32 fleet and went solely to ERJ 135/145 aircraft.\n\nOn February 5, 2020, Contour Airlines announced that it would add [[Indianapolis International Airport|Indianapolis]] as a focus city and purchase additional [[Embraer ERJ family|ERJ-135/145]] aircraft. The airline plans to serve [[Nashville International Airport|Nashville]], [[Pittsburgh International Airport|Pittsburgh]] and [[St. Louis Lambert International Airport|St. Louis]] from Indianapolis beginning June 10, 2020.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https: